            </def>
         </nym>
         <nym xml:id="chemical_184">
            <form>shell limestone</form>
            <def>
               <p>A type of limestone composed largely of shells.</p>
            </def>
         </nym>
         <nym xml:id="chemical_088">
            <form>sandstone</form>
            <def>
               <p>A sedimentary rock consisting of sand or quartz grains cemented together, typically red, yellow, or brown in colour.</p>
            </def>
         </nym>
         <nym xml:id="chemical_185">
            <form>ironstone</form>
            <def>
               <p>A sedimentary rock, either deposited directly as a ferruginous sediment or created by chemical replacement, that contains a substantial proportion of an iron ore compound.</p>
            </def>
         </nym>
         <nym xml:id="chemical_189">
            <form>molybdic acid</form>
            <def>
               <p>Symbol/formula: MoO3Â·H2O</p>
